## 6. Strengths

| # | Area | Details |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | **Intelligent Multi-Phase Pipeline** | The 4-phase approach (extraction → code gen → execution → interpretation) generates executable pandas code, runs it in a sandbox, then has Gemini interpret computed results. More accurate analyses at lower token cost. |
| 2 | **Service Layer Architecture** | Analysis pipeline extracted to `services/analysis_pipeline.py` — decoupled from server routing. Dashboard persistence in `services/dashboard_store.py` with normalized store schema. Each function owns a single decision level and can be tested independently. |
| 3 | **Multi-Session Chat System** | `chat_session_service.py` (300 lines) manages multiple conversation sessions per user. Features: create/activate/delete sessions, auto-derive titles from first user message, v2 persistence format with backward-compatible legacy migration, per-session token usage tracking. |
| 4 | **Token Usage & Cost Tracking** | `usage_service.py` (174 lines) tracks input/output tokens per LLM call, computes costs using Gemini Flash Lite pricing ($0.25/M input, $1.50/M output), converts to MYR, and provides a request budget summary with remaining requests and reset timers. Persisted across sessions. |
| 5 | **Custom Exception Hierarchy** | `errors.py` defines 7 typed exceptions (`DataTalkError`, `AuthenticationError`, `DatasetNotFoundError`, `LLMServiceError`, `CodeExecutionError`, `ValidationError`, `DataProcessingError`) each mapped to HTTP status codes. Caught by a global Flask error handler for consistent API responses. |
| 6 | **Real Authentication & Multi-User Support** | Supabase Auth with email/password signup, JWT verification via `@require_auth` decorator on all API routes. Per-user `UserState` isolated by `user_id` from JWT. Thread-safe `SessionManager` with TTL-based eviction (`SESSION_TTL_SECONDS`). `remove_state()` called on logout. |
| 7 | **Persistent Storage Layer** | Supabase PostgreSQL with `profiles`, `chat_sessions`, `dashboard_configs` tables and Row Level Security. File uploads stored in Supabase Storage with per-user directory isolation. Session rehydration on login. v2 persistence format for chat sessions with backward-compatible migration. |
| 8 | **Sandbox Security (Defense-in-Depth)** | `code_executor.py` implements 4 layers: code length cap (10K chars), AST-based static analysis via `_SafetyVisitor`, 19 blocked builtins + 9 forbidden modules + 14 forbidden attributes, restricted builtins dict, and a 60-second timeout enforced in a spawned child process. |
| 9 | **Smart Data Profiling** | `data_service.py` auto-detects dataset types (survey, time series, transactional, categorical, numerical) and generates domain-specific analysis suggestions. Provides the LLM with richer context, significantly improving output quality. |
| 10 | **Token-Efficient Context Building** | Schema context is dynamically sized with a `max_tokens` budget. Correlations are computed locally, only metadata sent to the LLM. The extraction phase pulls out unique categorical values so the code generator knows exact column names — prevents hallucinated column references. |
| 11 | **Per-User DataFrame Caching** | Loaded DataFrames are cached in `UserState._file_cache` after first download. Schema contexts (lean + full) and data profiles are also cached per file. Invalidated on new upload. Prevents re-downloading from Supabase on every chat message. |
| 12 | **SSE Streaming Responses** | `/api/chat/stream` endpoint streams pipeline phases in real-time via Server-Sent Events. Frontend shows live progress updates (loading → extracting → generating → executing → interpreting) instead of a static spinner. |
| 13 | **Graceful Degradation** | Code execution has 2 retry attempts with error feedback to Gemini, plus a text-only fallback (Phase 3). If code fails completely, users still get useful analysis. Cached results show a "Cached" badge for transparency. |
| 14 | **GridStack Dashboard** | Replaced custom CSS grid with GridStack library for drag-and-drop widget management. Supports: chart widgets + KPI card widgets, resize handles, position persistence to Supabase, chart customizer overlay, shared Plotly resize observer, and per-session scoping. |
| 15 | **Profile Management** | `profile.html` provides a standalone account settings page with display name editing, avatar initials auto-generation, responsive layout, and session validation. Backend `POST /api/profile` endpoint with `auth_service.update_profile()`. |
| 16 | **Error Toast System** | Frontend `showErrorToast()` provides branded, auto-dismissing error notifications. `showAppError()` handles both inline and toast display. Replaced many `alert()` calls with proper UI feedback. |
| 17 | **Polished UI with Custom Brand** | Pink/navy/beige brand palette with 7 custom illustrated character assets. Bento grid layout for landing page. Smooth micro-interactions (hover lifts, gradient avatars, animated typing dots). CSS containment for scroll performance. |
| 18 | **Unified Theme Tokens** | Shared CSS variables power a consistent single-theme experience across all UI surfaces and dashboard modules. |
| 19 | **Clean Modular CSS** | Stylesheets are organized by concern in `/css/`: `styles.css` (global/landing), `dashboard-layout.css` (layout + visualisation grid), `dashboard-chat.css` (chat + overlay UI), and `data-dashboard.css` (GridStack/dashboard overrides). The old `dashboard.css`, `dashboard-grid.css`, and `dashboard-overlays.css` split files were removed after consolidation. |
| 20 | **Consistent Structured Logging** | All backend services use Python's `logging` module with named loggers (`data_talk`, `data_talk.auth`, `data_talk.gemini`). `_log_event()` emits structured JSON logs. `_record_and_log_usage()` persists token usage to state and emits logs. |
| 21 | **DOMPurify XSS Prevention** | All user-generated and LLM-generated markdown is sanitised through a `marked.js` → `DOMPurify` pipeline before DOM insertion. Custom `escapeHtml()` fallback if DOMPurify is unavailable. |
| 22 | **Per-User Query Caching** | LRU cache (configurable, default 300 items) per user prevents redundant API calls for repeated questions, saving both time and API costs. Thread-safe via `threading.Lock`. |
| 23 | **Paginated Chat History** | `/api/chat/history` supports `?page=&per_page=` query parameters with metadata (`total`, `total_pages`). The shared paginator now lives in `src/core/pagination.py`, keeping route files focused on request handling. |
| 24 | **Configurable via Environment** | `app_config.py` (85 lines) centralizes all configuration: `MAX_RETRIES`, `CHAT_HISTORY_CAP`, `QUERY_CACHE_SIZE`, `EXEC_TIMEOUT`, `RATE_LIMIT`, `USD_TO_MYR_RATE`, `SESSION_TTL_SECONDS`, pagination defaults, Supabase URLs, SSL paths. Type-safe getters (`get_bool_env`, `get_int_env`, `get_float_env`). |
| 25 | **All Dependencies Pinned** | `requirements.txt` pins exact versions for all 11 packages — excellent for reproducibility and security. |
| 26 | **Path Traversal Prevention** | `data_service.py` normalizes all storage paths via `_normalize_relative_path()` with `secure_filename()` and explicit `..` traversal blocking. |

