## 7. Weaknesses

### 7.1 Critical Issues

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **Broken Logout Flow** | `logout()` now creates a fresh Supabase client and updates its headers, but it never calls `sign_out()` or returns success. The route no longer invalidates the session token reliably. | `auth_service.py` lines 278-289 |
| 2 | **No Full Data Pagination** | `get_full_data()` still loads the entire dataset into memory and sends it as JSON. Large files will cause memory and bandwidth issues. `chat/history` is paginated, but `/api/data/<filename>` remains a full payload endpoint. | `server.py` lines 438-449 |

### 7.2 Security Concerns

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **Zero SRI Hashes on All CDN Resources** | Handsontable, SheetJS, Plotly.js, Marked.js, DOMPurify, and GridStack (3 resources) all loaded without `integrity` or `crossorigin` attributes. A compromised CDN could inject arbitrary JavaScript with full access to auth tokens and data. Now 9 CDN resources total without SRI. | `dashboard.html` |
| 2 | **Unpinned CDN Versions** | SheetJS uses `xlsx-latest`, Handsontable and Marked.js use unpinned `npm/...` URLs. GridStack uses `@10` (major) but not a specific minor version. Supply-chain attack risk. | `dashboard.html` |
| 3 | **localStorage Token Storage** | `dt_access_token`, `dt_refresh_token`, and `dt_user` stored in `localStorage`, accessible to any JS on the page including scripts from compromised CDNs. `httpOnly` cookies would be more secure. | `login.html`, `profile.html`, `core.js` |
| 4 | **No Prompt Injection Protection** | User questions are interpolated directly into LLM prompts. A crafted question could manipulate the system prompt, causing unintended code generation. | `gemini_service.py` |
| 5 | **Sandbox Escape Residual Risk** | While AST validation blocks known dangerous patterns, `type()`, `vars()`, `dir()`, and `hasattr()` remain in safe builtins. The sandbox now runs in a spawned child process, so timeout handling is stronger, but it is still not a hard security boundary. | `code_executor.py` |
| 6 | **No Token Refresh Endpoint** | The server returns `refresh_token` on login, but no endpoint exists to refresh an expired access token. Users must re-authenticate when tokens expire. | `auth_service.py` |
| 7 | **Token Verified via Network on Every Request** | `verify_token()` calls Supabase `getUser()` API on every authenticated request. No local JWT validation or caching. Adds latency and creates a dependency on Supabase availability. | `auth_service.py` line 130 |

### 7.3 Performance Issues

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **DataFrame Copied Per Execution** | Full DataFrame is `.copy()`'d for every code execution call — doubles memory for large files. | `code_executor.py` line 157 |
| 2 | **O(n²) Correlation Computation** | Numeric correlation matrix computed for all column pairs — slow/expensive with 100+ columns. | `data_service.py` lines 228-245 |
| 3 | **Particle Animation O(n²)** | `connectParticles()` computes distance for every particle pair every frame. On 1920×1080: ~230 particles, ~26,000 comparisons per frame at 60fps. | `js/core.js` lines 219-244 |
| 4 | **Plotly Resize Stabilization** | `schedulePlotlyStabilizeResize()` fires 4 staggered resize calls (120ms, 260ms, 450ms, 700ms) per chart after GridStack changes. With many widgets, this creates significant rendering churn. | `js/dashboard-ui.js` lines 295-304 |

### 7.4 Code Quality Issues

| # | Area | Details | Location |
|---|------|---------|----------|
| 1 | **Zero Test Coverage** | No unit tests, integration tests, or end-to-end tests for any component. The sandbox, data parsing, API endpoints, chat session service, usage service, and auth are all untested. `.gitignore` includes `.pytest_cache/` but no tests exist. | Entire project |
| 2 | **No Module System (Frontend)** | All frontend functions are globals on `window` scope (~90+ functions across data-chat.js, dashboard-ui.js, core.js). No ES modules, no bundler. Load order dependencies between files (e.g., `core.js` must load before `data-chat.js`). | All JS files |
| 3 | **No JSDoc / Minimal Docstrings** | Frontend functions have no documentation. Backend has docstrings for most public functions but many internal helpers lack them. Parameter expectations unclear across service boundaries. | All files |
| 4 | **Duplicate CSS: Suggestion Chips** | `.suggestion-chip` / `.suggestions-row` defined in both `styles.css` (landing page) and `dashboard-chat.css` (dashboard). Minor inconsistencies in font-size (0.9rem vs 0.88rem). | CSS files |
| 5 | **Duplicate Auth Utils** | `profile.html` reimplements `getAuthHeaders()`, `signOut()`, and token storage patterns that already exist in `core.js`. No shared utility module. | `profile.html`, `js/core.js` |

### 7.5 UX / Accessibility Issues

| # | Area | Details |
|---|------|---------|
| 1 | **No Responsive Design for Dashboard** | Sidebar is fixed 260px with no collapse mechanism on mobile. GridStack dashboard has no responsive breakpoints. The app is desktop-only. (Profile page is responsive.) |
| 2 | **Sidebar Nav Items Not Keyboard-Accessible** | Nav items use `<div onclick>` instead of `<button>` or `<a>`. Not focusable via Tab, no `role="button"`, no keyboard event handlers. |
| 3 | **No Skip Navigation Links** | No skip-to-content link for keyboard users. No ARIA live regions for chat status changes in the dashboard. |
| 4 | **Residual `confirm()` Dialogs** | `removeDashChart()` and `clearAllCharts()` still use browser `confirm()` dialogs for deletion confirmation. Inconsistent with the polished UI. |
| 5 | **Handsontable License** | Uses `"non-commercial-and-evaluation"` license key. Must verify this is appropriate for the intended use case. |
| 6 | **No ARIA Live Regions** | Login form error/success messages are not announced to screen readers. Status changes in chat (loading, phase updates) have no ARIA announcements. (Profile page does have `aria-live="polite"` on status messages — a good pattern not yet applied to dashboard.) |

